      • getMvpDelegate

        protected ActivityMvpDelegate<V,P> getMvpDelegate()
        Get the mvp delegate. This is internally used for creating presenter, attaching and detaching view from presenter.

        Please note that only one instance of mvp delegate should be used per Activity instance.

        Only override this method if you really know what you are doing.

        Returns:
        ActivityMvpDelegateImpl

      • shouldInstanceBeRetained

        public boolean shouldInstanceBeRetained()
        Description copied from interface: BaseMvpDelegateCallback
        Indicates whether or not the the view will be retained during next screen orientation change. This boolean flag is used for MvpPresenter.detachView(boolean) as parameter. Usually you should take Activity#isChangingConfigurations() into account. The difference between BaseMvpDelegateCallback.shouldInstanceBeRetained() and BaseMvpDelegateCallback.isRetainInstance() is that BaseMvpDelegateCallback.isRetainInstance() indicates that retain instance feature is enabled or disabled while BaseMvpDelegateCallback.shouldInstanceBeRetained() indicates if the view is going to be destroyed permanently and hence should no more be retained (i.e. Activity is finishing and not just screen orientation changing)
        Specified by:
        shouldInstanceBeRetained in interface BaseMvpDelegateCallback<V extends MvpView,P extends MvpPresenter<V>>
        Returns:
        true if the instance should be retained, otherwise false

      • onRetainNonMosbyCustomNonConfigurationInstance

        public java.lang.Object onRetainNonMosbyCustomNonConfigurationInstance()
        Description copied from interface: ActivityMvpDelegateCallback
        Return any Object holding the desired state to propagate to the next activity instance. Please note that mosby internals like the presenter are already saved internally and you don't have to take them into account. You can retrieve this value later with ActivityMvpDelegate.getNonMosbyLastCustomNonConfigurationInstance().

        This mechanism works pretty the same way as FragmentActivity#onRetainCustomNonConfigurationInstance() and ActivityMvpDelegateCallback.getNonMosbyLastCustomNonConfigurationInstance()

        Specified by:
        onRetainNonMosbyCustomNonConfigurationInstance in interface ActivityMvpDelegateCallback<V extends MvpView,P extends MvpPresenter<V>>
        Returns:
        Object holding state.

      • onRetainCustomNonConfigurationInstance

      • getNonMosbyLastCustomNonConfigurationInstance

        public final java.lang.Object getNonMosbyLastCustomNonConfigurationInstance()
        Description copied from interface: ActivityMvpDelegateCallback
        This method should invoke ActivityMvpDelegate.getNonMosbyLastCustomNonConfigurationInstance().

        This method is not really a "callback" method (will not invoked from delegate somehow). However, it's part of this interface to ensure that no custom implementation will miss this method since this method is the counterpart to ActivityMvpDelegateCallback.onRetainNonMosbyCustomNonConfigurationInstance()

        Specified by:
        getNonMosbyLastCustomNonConfigurationInstance in interface ActivityMvpDelegateCallback<V extends MvpView,P extends MvpPresenter<V>>
